The Power Spear is a rare and specialized variant of the standard Power Weapon, designed for warriors who favor reach and the devastating impact of a charge over sustained close-quarters dueling. The weapon features an elongated haft tipped with a broad, energy-wreathed blade, allowing its wielder to strike with tremendous momentum when closing with the enemy. On the charge, the Power Spear concentrates immense kinetic force through its disruption field, punching through heavy armor with ease; once the initial clash subsides, the weapon remains a capable if less penetrating tool in a prolonged melee.  
Power Spears are most commonly associated with honor guards, Chapter champions, and those warriors drawn from cultures with strong spear-fighting traditions. The White Scars, with their emphasis on the devastating mounted charge, are among the most prolific users of the Power Spear, wielding them from the saddle of their bikes to deadly effect. Other Chapters reserve the Power Spear for ceremonial guard units or as marks of distinction for warriors who have proven themselves in the art of the charge. Whatever its origin, the Power Spear rewards aggressive tactics and decisive action, embodying the offensive spirit of the Adeptus Astartes.

**Power Sword**		

