# **FORCE ORGANIZATION**

### **Relics of the Past**

From the depths of the most secure vaults and secretive halls of the Chapter, a few revered war machines of the Great Crusade and Horus Heresy still endure. These vehicles, known as Relics of the Past, carry the legacy of the Imperium’s most glorious and tumultuous era. Each is a marvel of ancient technology, brimming with the secrets of a bygone age. Due to their rarity and the immense reverence in which they are held, the deployment of these relics is strictly controlled, with only a select few permitted to see the battlefield.

An army may include only one vehicle with the Relic of the Past special rule for every full 1000 points in the army list’s point limit. For example, in a 2000-point army, up to two vehicles with the Relic of the Past special rule may be included. If the point limit is 1500, only one such vehicle may be fielded, as there is only one full multiple of 1000 in the point limit.

### **Volkite Limit**

The ancient and potent Volkite weapons are relics of a bygone era, their secrets known to only a few within the Imperium. These rare and powerful armaments are jealously guarded by those Chapters fortunate enough to possess them, ensuring they are only deployed in the most dire of circumstances.  

Due to this, a Space Marine army may field only one Volkite weapon for every full 500 points in the army list’s point limit. For example, in a 2000-point army, up to four Volkite weapons may be included. If the point limit is 800, only one Volkite weapon may be fielded, as there is only one full multiple of 500 in the point limit.  If a model is equipped with multiple Volkite weapons, each Volkite weapon still counts toward the limit.  Twin-linked Volkite weapons count as a single weapon.

