# **IMPERIAL FISTS**

## **Special Rules**

### **Indomitable Defense**

Models with Imperial Fists Chapter Tactics gain an additional \+1 to their Cover Save, enhancing their durability when holding defensive positions. This bonus only applies if the unit already benefits from a cover save from another source. If the unit does not have a cover save initially, this bonus does not apply.

### **Bolter Drills**

All Bolter weapons (Bolter, Bolt Pistol, Hurricane Bolter, etc.) wielded by units with Imperial Fists ***Chapter Tactics*** re-roll failed to hit rolls of 1\.

### **Shield-Captain**

At the start of your turn, select one friendly Imperial Fists unit within 6" of the Shield-Captain. Until the start of your next turn, that unit gains a 5+ invulnerable save against ranged attacks.

## **Force Organization**

* Any Imperial Fists model with the Infantry (Character) or Bike (Character) type may upgrade to Artificer Armor for 10 points, representing their emphasis on durability and holding the line.  
* Any Imperial Fists model with the Infantry (Character) or Bike (Character) type may be upgraded to be Shield-Captain for 10 points.  
* Imperial Fists may take one Heavy Support unit per detachment without it occupying Force Organization slots. This unit must be either a Devastator Squad, Centurion Devastator Squad, or Whirlwinds. However, they cannot be used as compulsory Troops choices for any reason.

## **Imperial Fists Wargear**

# **IRON HANDS**

## **Special Rules**

### **The Flesh is Weak**

All models with the Iron Hands ***Chapter Tactics*** rule have a 6+ Feel No Pain (FNP) roll. Every additional source of Feel No Pain increases the FNP target by \+1, to a maximum of 2+.  If the model already had a source of FNP that is better than that afforded by The Flesh is Weak, they instead add \+1 to that FNP roll. Additionally, any non-vehicle model may take Bionics as Wargear, even if they do not normally have access to it.

### **Calculated Fury**

When shooting or in close combat, a unit with the Iron Hands **Chapter Tactics** may reroll failed to-hit rolls of 1, but only if the unit did not move in their preceding Movement phase. This rule reflects their tactical preference for calculated, deliberate strikes rather than hasty attacks.

### **Iron Father**

A model with the Iron Father Special Rule gains \+1 Ld and any models wholly within 6” of the Iron Father may use the Iron Father’s Leadership in place of their own for all Morale tests.

## **Force Organization**

* The Iron Hands have a deep distrust of the warp and psykers.  Because of this, a detachment of Iron Hands Space Marines may only ever have a maximum of 1 selection of units with the **Psyker** Special Rule, and may only take a Librarian if they have another HQ selection in the detachment.  An Iron Hands Librarian may never be selected as the Warlord.  
* Any Iron Hands model with the Infantry (Character) or Bike (Character) type may be upgraded to be an Iron Father for 10 points.  
* Up to one Techmarine per detachment may be taken without using a Force Organization slot.  This techmarine must be taken as the basic profile and may not buy any upgrades, but the Techmarine may still buy Servitors.  A Techmarine taken in this way does not count in regards to any rules that require or limit the number of HQs and Iron Hands may take Techmarines in the HQ slot as normal.  
* Iron Hands Veteran Sergeants may take Indomitus Terminator Armor.  If they do, they must replace their Boltgun and Bolt Pistol with a Power Fist and Storm Bolter.  This costs 21 points per model.  The Veteran Sergeant may purchase upgrades as a Terminator from a Terminator Squad.

